The paper discusses the optimization of convolutional highway networks using an evolutionary algorithm, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). The networks are specifically designed for image classification tasks, which is a common application of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of hyperparameters and structure optimization, which are common topics in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The use of an evolutionary algorithm for optimization is a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for using these networks in control systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
